The "ForbinÃ¢â‚¬â„¢s" narration included a reference to The Talking HeadsÃ¢â‚¬â„¢ David Byrne. 
The second set "musical costume" was The Talking Heads' album Remain in Light -- all songs were Phish debuts. 
Mike sat in an armchair to sing "Seen and Not Seen." 
The set featured Karl Perazzo on percussion, Dave Grippo on saxophone, and Gary Gazaway on trumpet. 
Perazzo also played during the third set. "Jesus Just Left Chicago," "Suzy Greenberg," and "Frankenstein" also featured Grippo and Gazaway. 
The third set included Remain in Light teases.
